{{see|Rebel}}
==English==

===Etymology 1===
French ''[[rebelle]]'' &gt; Latin ''[[rebellis]]'' (waging war again, insurgent)

====Pronunciation====
*rĕb'əl, /ˈrɛbəl/, /<tt>"rEb@l</tt>/

====Noun====
'''rebel''' (''plural'' '''[[rebels]]''')

#A person who [[resist]]s an established [[authority]], often [[violently]].

