===Etymology 2===
French ''[[rebeller]]'' &gt; Latin ''[[rebellare]]'' (to fight back, to wage war again)

====Pronunciation====
*rĭbəl', /rɪbəlˈ/, /<tt>rI"b@l</tt>/

====Intransitive verb====
{{en-verb|rebel|l|ing}}

#To [[resist]] or become [[defiant]] toward an [[authority]].

